\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. P. tetraphyllum} (L.) L., {\i Syst. Nat.} ed. 10, {\b 2:} 881 (1759).Annual, biennial or perennial, without a woody stock; stems simple or much-branched. Leaves obovate. Inflorescence lax, spreading, much-branched. Sepals c. 2 mm; petals usually emarginate.{\i  S. & W. Europe.} Al Az Bl Br Bu Co Cr Ga Ge Gr He Hs It Ju Lu Sa Si Tu [Be Cz].
\par
\par
