\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 20.             Ortegia}                L.
\par  
\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By A.O. Chater.
\par
\par
\pard\f0\fs28 Small plant with opposite leaves. Flowers small, shortly pedicellate in opposite, cymose clusters which are arranged in a panicle. Sepals 5, keeled, the margins scarious; petals absent; stamens 3; style 1, stigma 3-toothed or -lobed. Capsule dehiscing with 3 valves. Seeds numerous, minute, ovoid, acute.
\par
\par
\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. O. hispanica} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 560 (1753) ({\i O. dichotoma} L.). Annual to perennial; stems up to 40 cm, with many strict branches, angular, often very rough above. Leaves 5-18 mm, opposite, linear or linear-lanceolate, obtuse or acute, much shorter than the internodes, erect; stipules setiform, caducous, with blackish glands. Sepals 2-3 mm, ovate-lanceolate, acute, keeled, green, with scarious margins. {\i Spain and Portugal}. Hs †It Lu.
