\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 21.           Loeflingia}              L.
\par    
\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By V.H. Heywood.
\par
\par
\pard\f0\fs28 Annuals. Flowers small, sessile, in compound dichasial or monochasial cymes, often spicate. Sepals free, unequal, the outer 3 longer and wider than the inner 2, all or only the outer with a setiform appendage on each side; petals 3 or 5, very small; stamens 3 or 5; style 1; stigmas 3, or 1, more or less 3-lobed. Fruit a capsule dehiscing with 3 valves. Seeds numerous.
