\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. L. hispanica} L., {\i Sp. Pl. }35 (1753) ({\i L. hispanica} var. {\i pentandra} sensu Coutinho; incl. {\i L. pentandra} Cav.). Much-branched, glandular-pubescent annual 2-10 cm. Leaves linear, acute, connate at the base with the subulate stipules. Inflorescence-branches more or less condensed, not secund. Sepals (2-)2*5-3 mm, all with setiform appendages; stamens usually 3; style about 1/2 as long as the capsule; stigma usually only shallowly lobed. {\i Sandy soils. W. Mediterranean region.} Bl Ga Hs Lu Si.
\par
\par
\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. L. baetica} Lag.,{\i  Period. Soc. Med. Cádiz}{\b  4}({\b 1}): 5 (1824) ({\i L. hispanica} var.{\i  micrantha} (Boiss. & Reuter) Maire; incl.{\i  L. gaditana }Boiss. & Reuter, {\i L. micrantha }Boiss. & Reuter). Like {\b 1} but sepals 1·5-2 mm, only 3 with setiform appendages; stamens 5; style as long as the capsule.{\i  Maritime sands. S. Spain; C. & S. Portugal}. Hs Lu.
